-- Regulator Probing Cotton Trading, Losses, Financial Times Says
-- B y   S t e v e   S t r o t h
-- 2012-05-23T20:26:32Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-23/regulator-probing-cotton-trading-losses-financial-times-says.html
The Commodity Futures Trading
Commission is interviewing cotton industry officials as part of
a probe of trading that resulted in losses last year for
commodities trader  Glencore International Plc (GLEN) , the Financial
Times  reported .  Traders are being asked about the large number of cotton
bales delivered through the ICE Futures U.S. exchange in
mid-2011, the Financial Times reported, citing industry
executives and companies, which the newspaper didn’t identify,
that were contacted by the agency.  CFTC investigators are seeking information from merchants
including Louis Dreyfus Commodities, Olam International, Cargill
Inc., Nobel Group and Glencore, the newspaper said, citing
people familiar with the probe that weren’t identified.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Steve Stroth in Chicago at 
